================================================================================
§7  RUST CODE CONVENTIONS
================================================================================

7.1  MODULE ORGANIZATION
    - Core logic: `core/src/`
    - Mobile bindings: `mobile/src/`
    - WASM bindings: `wasm/src/`

7.2  ASYNC PATTERNS
    - Use tokio runtime for all async operations
    - Prefer `async fn` over `impl Future`
    - Use `tokio::spawn` for concurrent tasks

7.3  ERROR HANDLING
    - Use `thiserror` for error types
    - Use `anyhow` for error propagation in binaries
    - Propagate errors with `?` operator
    - NEVER panic in library code
    - NEVER use `unwrap()` in library code (use `?` or `expect()` with context)

7.4  UNIFFI INTEGRATION
    - All public API functions must be in `core/src/api.udl`
    - Use `#[uniffi::export]` for exported functions
    - Test bindings after ANY API changes
    - Regenerate Swift/Kotlin stubs via `uniffi-bindgen`

7.5  LOGGING
    - Use `tracing` for logging (not `println!` in library code)
    - Use `tracing-subscriber` for configuration

7.6  CONCURRENCY
    - Use `parking_lot::RwLock` over `std::sync::RwLock`
    - `IronCore` uses `Arc<RwLock<_>>` internals — cheap to clone, thread-safe

7.7  SERIALIZATION
    - `bincode` for wire format
    - `serde_json` for human-readable/debug

